Mobiles.LongDescription: A young member of the town militia looks bored with his guard duty.
Mobiles.Description: This young man looks recently recruited from the outlying farms, helikely hasn't had much experience though is well trained.  He seems to bewaiting desperately for something exciting to happen.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Loris looks up from feeding his fish as you enter.
Mobiles.Description: Loris' gentle smile is known throughout the Realm, and it is a subject ofmuch speculation just how this chubby, soft-spoken man survived his time asan adventurer and earned enough treasure to open up his famous Thesden shop.Light reflects a bit off the top of his head, which is round and hairless asan egg.  Still, Loris seems happy in his quiet life, tending his animals,and ordering in goodies from the bakery.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A fluffy white cat purrs happily here.
A trained copperhead snake slithers along here.
Mobiles.Description: This snake is about four feet long and colored a copperish red.  It'sfangs drip lethal poison.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A loyal guard dog sniffs the air here.
Mobiles.Description: This dog looks very alert, its pointy ears darting back and forth.  Iteyes you warily.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A black-winged falcon is perched nearby.
A smoky-grey hamster looks for somewhere to hide.

Mobiles.NameForTargeting: furniture thin man aaron dickhead bastard fucker shithead wolsey
Mobiles.LongDescription: A thin, meticulously dressed man smiles slightly and offers a price list.
Mobiles.Description: This short, thin man is dressed in neatly pressed somber colored cottonclothes.  Aaron Wolsey has a lizard-like quality to him, and makes you feelquite uncomfortable as you decide what to buy.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A grizzled, wiry man points to a drink list behind the bar.
Mobiles.Description: Daran is probably in his late middle years, his once-strong muscles justbeginning to fail him.  He used to work as an executioner for the town, andsince has moved on to open this tavern, no one is really sure why he quit,he doesn't talk about it...

Mobiles.LongDescription: An aged woman with half-closed eyes smiles at you strangely.
Mobiles.Description: Zannah's past is a mystery, she has worked here in Thesden as long asanyone can remember.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tall, thin man with thick black hair asks if you would like a room.
Mobiles.Description: Hazel eyes sparkle at you from above a mustache turning silver with age,as the Innkeeper returns your curious gaze with one of his own.  He smiles,and pours himself another ale.  The ale disappears at an amazing rate, andhe tidies up his business, moving chairs fussily, carefully.  His nose is abit red, and his eyes just a bit bleary, but his actions are unimpaired.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Shopkeeper template
Simon is here, collecting wax from a dripping candle.
An old weather-beaten man is here, a long scar along his cheek.
Mobiles.Description: A reformed pirate, Mincer Ray retired to Thesden once he was grantedamnesty by the King.  His years show in the deep wrinkles on his face andthinning grey hair, but he still moves with surprising speed when he wishes.Local rumor even whispers of a torrid affair with another retiredadventurer, but Mincer Ray only smiles and winks when asked.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sweaty man in a blood-stained apron is slicing meat here.
A young farmer is here, tending her carts.
Mobiles.Description: Young, but with hands roughened from field work, this girl smiles shylyat you from behind her produce cart.  Her clothing shows smudges and dirt,which show the fading of an outfit carefully (but not successfully) cleanedafter a hard day's labor.  Although she is the youngest of the sellers here,her produce looks very fresh and clean, and in better shape than the otherfarmers' products.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A pale, black haired woman is arranging some violets in a vase here.
Mobiles.Description: A thin part-elven woman leans casually against the counter as shearranges some bright purple flowers and places them in a crystal vase.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tired-looking heavyset man is waiting impatiently for you to buy something.
A young man looks up from stretching a deer pelt as you enter.
Mobiles.Description: The tanner looks up, and you catch a glimpse of warm brown eyes, beforehe lowers them again to his work.  Known for his reluctance to speak, themerchant is still one of the more popular shopkeepers in town, for thequality of his waterskins.  While he is young to have his own shop, he isundeniably an artist.  His clever hands are rarely ever still, whetherchecking a pelt being stretched, or carefully softening a pair of half-doneboots, already incredibly soft, in the small size of a woman.  When asked,he will say only that the boots are not for sale.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An aging man in brown robes is scribbling in a thick notebook here.
Mobiles.Description: Although clearly aging, Narcissus bears himself like a much younger man.His slim form, slightly stooped from years of bending over books, moves in asprightly manner through the crowded shelves of his shop.  A bright goldring glints on his finger, and a slight smile hovers on his lips.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A melancholy young woman is here, tapping her fingers on the counter.
Mobiles.Description: The familiarity of the curve of her cheeks, and the movement of her darkhair is puzzling for a moment, until she moves to tidy under the picture ofthe brunette, which is, clearly her.  However, while the painting shows noimperfections, Lyra is a merely pretty girl, with all the usual flaws ofhumanity.  She watches everyone in the shop with skeptical eyes, toying withan intricately-detailed leather belt.  She waits for her customers to make apurchase or leave, her thoughts her own.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A man in a black apron is here, holding a piece of molten silver in some tongs.
Mobiles.Description: Ith is a huge man, bulging biceps and wide chest.  Yet his work isdelicate and sublime, carefully crafted and beautiful.  Trained by Hugardthe armorer in iron-work, Ith's interest quickly diverted to the finercrafts of smithing.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The baker is here, frantically trying to take orders and cook at the same time.
Mobiles.Description: Never trust the food baked by a thin man.  If that's true, then thisbaker's food must be delicious!  This man is enormously round, but he seemspretty happy, if impatient.  His apron bears smudges of chocolate, whatlooks like jam, and smells of flour and vanilla.  Moving with a grace thatbelies his ponderous girth and quadruple chins, he has all the efficiencyand joy of someone who truly loves his job.

Mobiles.LongDescription: (no long description)
A small pony is here, looking for some grass.
`aSpink adjusts his`o s`kp`oa`kr`ok`kl`oi`kn`og`a jacket as he is prancing around the shop.``
Mobiles.Description: `aHere stands the most successful burglar and pickpocket in the historyof Thesden, Spink.  Being cross-eyed, scrawny and having a pair of peg-legsinstead of feet, he is hardly the image of a criminal mastermind, perhapsthat played a part in his success.  Retired, he now runs this curiousityshop, selling the items that he has 'aquired' over the years.  Though yoususpect that he is keeping the good stuff to himself.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A pink elephant balances on its trunk here.
Mobiles.Description: `mSo this is where that pink elephant that has been talking to you inyour dreams is!  It always seemed much bigger and more charismatic in yourdreams...  It has a nice trunk though.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fSmiling stupidly, a purple camel occupies the stairs here.``
``Amedeo is here, examining a sparkling`j green`` stone.
A small harmless feline searches for food.
Mobiles.Description: An alley cat returns your stare suspiciously, and then dismisses you witha flick of its tail.  As you have not produced food for it, it has decidedto clean its neither regions to show you exactly where you stand on thegrand scheme of things.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Citizen template
The clothier is here, patching an old jacket.
Mobiles.Description: A large, strong-looking man, the clothier looks at first to be morecapable of wielding a sword than a needle and thread.  Those who knowSamuel, however, know that his size is deceptive, for the clothier isincredibly nimble with a needle, but deathly ill at the sight of blood.  Agehas treated him as it treats most men, adding a bit of extra weight here andthere, and coloring the hair left in his receding hairline with grey amongthe darker brown strands.  Always nattily attired, the clothier wears hisown goods with a certain amount of flair, if little flash.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sullen mule paces about.
`aan old grey horse mills about here.``
`dA chesnut colored quarter-horse stands here.``
`ka golden-coated horse struts proudly here.``
A draft work horse stands here.
`da strong clydesdale draft horse is here``
`aa black percheron warhorse stands proudly here.``
`oa white warhorse stands here proudly.``
The stablemaster is here, grooming a tottering young colt.
A rugged, bearded young man is fixing a frayed rope here.
Mobiles.Description: Tall, lean, and healthy looking, Thyrn is dressed completely in thelatest survival gear, none of which has a spot of dirt or wear upon it.Although he seems to be repairing a rope readily enough, his hands have noneof the calluses you see on the hands of an adventurer, or even a physicallaborer.  Shaggy brown hair seems to have been deliberately cut uneven togive that uncut look, but his small beard is well trimmed.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The glass blower is here, carefully creating a masterpiece of molten glass.
Mobiles.Description: One of the finest craftsman of this era, Brielle is here carefullyinserting a bubble into the ball of molten glass he is creating.  He iscovered in sweat from the heat of the furnace and applying his trade.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A handsome young stable boy is here, selling supplies.
Mobiles.Description: With Evyns cap of burnished russet hair, and charming dimpledsmile, it's no wonder all of Thesden's young ladies flockto the Gray Gelding Stable, cooing adoration.  But a glintin his eye belies dreams of exploration and adventure, not ofhusbandry, which he hopes someday to experience after hisapprenticeship ends.  As he brushes the silken mane of achestnut hair, you can't help but admire his long slender fingers,and his smooth, steady touch.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The barkeep is here, serving drinks.
The potter is here, carefully applying glaze to a thin vase.
Mobiles.Description: Clara is a short woman who looks just over 30 years old.  Her hands, faceand clothes are marked with little dabs of clay and glaze, giving theimpression of someone who is always hard at work.  She came to Thesden fromPerthshire years ago, and has made quite a reputation for herself and herceramics among the nobility.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The armorer is here, ready to fit you for combat.
Mobiles.Description: Hugard was born the son of a farmer, and came to the city in his youth toapprentice to the black smith.  His age is catching up to him, grey hairreplacing brown, yet his arms are still quite powerful and you can expectthe best craftsmanship available this side of the sea.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tall man in silk robes watches you thoughtfully and taps his pipe.
Mobiles.Description: Sardin was born far from Thesden, on a distant island.  His father, asea-faring merchant, married and settled with an island woman.  His motherdied when he was young in a pirate raid, his father escaped with his lifeand young Sardin's.  Sardin grew into the profession of his father, butstays safely within the city walls.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A short, stocky man, wearing a leather apron, stands behind the counter.
Mobiles.Description: At a little prompting, John will break into elaborate tales of theadventures of his youth.  It's said he spent many of his teenage yearsliving among the secretive elves, far from other humans.  He has sincesettled, however, to working with his hands and creating practicalironworks.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A neatly dressed woman stands behind the counter waiting to help you.
Mobiles.Description: A slim, dark-haired woman of indeterminate age, Serra is a Thesdenfixture.  She dresses neatly but conservatively, in the manner of mostbankers.  Although the fabric of her garment is a fine, skillful weaving,the chaste cut of it and her manner make it clear that she is all business.The cut of her hair hides the tips of her ears, but her face is too round tobe elven, and too angular to be human.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A small rat skulks about in the shadows.
Mobiles.Description: This small, beady-eyed wonder sure looks like a rat.  Grey fur, quiveringwhiskerings, naked pink tail, and a predilection for cheese, this iscertainly a rat.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A mean-looking midget stands here glaring at you, the flowers in his hair are pink.
Mobiles.Description: `mThe mean and dangerous face of this muscly midget is made softer by thepink flowers braided into his hair.  And you would comment on his matchingpink lace dress, but that would only upset the poor guy.  Life is hardenough being a midget.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A stray dog sniffs the air here, looking for food.
Mobiles.Description: With that smell, the amount of drool, and the exuberantly stupid look inits eyes, this scrawny creature must be a dog.  A stick-like tail wags, andthe dog looks at around hopefully, telegraphing the fact that, you know, itcould eat that.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A young boy is playing in the dirt.
Mobiles.Description: A grungy young boy is kneeling and playing with some wooden dolls in thedirt.  You don't see any sign of a parent.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A young girl is playing with a toy wooden sword.
An old man is walking slowly by, aided by a wooden cane.
Mobiles.Description: This white-haired, slightly hunched old man makes his way slowly throughthe streets of Thesden.  He looks at you sadly, and hobbles on.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An old woman is carrying a basket of fruit, returning home from the market.
Mobiles.Description: This old woman is wearing plain dress, but walks with dignity through thedirty streets towards her home.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An old noble, in faded finery, is standing alone.
Mobiles.Description: This old aristocrat has clearly fallen on some hard times, his clothesare dirty and worn.  His eyes are fixed on the towers of castle Dunluce, agrim expression on his face.  He stands by himself, without any servants.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beggar in tattered rags begs for a coin.
Mobiles.Description: His face is coated in dirt, so that you can barely see his weary eyes andgrim, resigned mouth.  He holds a hand out to you, without a word, waving awooden bowl slightly as you walk by.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A merchant's apprentice is walking by hurriedly.
Mobiles.Description: Probably no older than 16, this young man looks incredibly tired as hewalk past you.  Likely, he is doing work as an apprentice to one of thelocal merchants.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA young farmer is carrying a heavy sack back to her farm.``
A poor merchant is looking for a place to trade his goods.
Mobiles.Description: His slightly tattered tunic and cape are clean, and well-taken care ofconsidering his impoverished circumstances.  He makes his way through thestreets looking for places to sell the goods he has to offer.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A drunken sailor on shore leave is staggering along the street.
Mobiles.Description: He walks unsteadily down the street, looking for a place to get more aleor vomit.  His tangled hair and ragged beard attest to many long days atsea, with few chances for rest.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tall, adolescent boy is leaning against the side of a building.
A young man sneers at you as you pass.
Mobiles.Description: This short, angry-looking young man is wearing dark brown studdedleather.  Drawings of dragons, snakes, and a broken-heart are burned intothe leather along the sleeves and back.  Raised on the bad side of town, hedoesn't seem to care much for his life or anyone else's.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A spectator is screaming for blood, waiting for the execution.
Mobiles.Description: A local, dressed in simple cotton clothes, is waiting excitedly for theexecution of the next prisoner; chanting for justice and taunting thecondemned man.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A farmer in from the fields wanders here, looking lost.
Mobiles.Description: A physically powerful man, his back wide and strong from many hours oflifting and tilling, this farmer's neck and arms are burnt and weathered bythe sun.  Dirt coats his face, and is crusted under his work-roughenedhands.  On the streets of the city, he is a stark contrast to those thatmove around him.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A strong sailor is carrying crates to the docks.
Mobiles.Description: The sailor has clearly been working a long time on the docks, he lookstired, his powerful arms straining.  Occasionally, he stops and looks outforlornly on Colwyn Bay, wishing for the roll of the sea beneath his feet.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A woman with a lute is playing for anyone who cares to listen.
Mobiles.Description: She plays the lute with ease, thoughtlessly as she sings and smiles atthe crowd.  Occasionally, she nods at an open sack lying at her feet with afew silver pieces in it.  She must not have been trained at the college,because anyone so talented who graduated from the college of music would bein a noble's court, not on the street.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A young nobleman stares down his nose at you.
Mobiles.Description: Dressed in an eminently impractical outfit of the finest cloth, completewith padded, bejeweled codpiece, this young man declares himself a noble bythe sheer wastefulness of most of his outfit.  A high cravat tucked into abow at his chin seems about to strangle him, and his legs have beencross-gartered so many times that it is amazing that all circulation in hislegs has not been cut off.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A young man is carrying a heavy bag of iron scraps here.
Mobiles.Description: You can tell easily, by looking at his hammer and powerful arms, thatthis young man works as a smith.  He is carrying a heavy bag of scrap iron,salvaged from the portcullis removed from the north gate.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A proud noble woman passes by, the crowd parting in front of her.
Mobiles.Description: The noble woman is wearing only the finest clothes, probably importedfrom distant lands.  Her movements are rehearsed and proper, no doubt aresult of her upbringing in a life or priviledge.  Her disdain for thecommoners around her is obvious as she strolls by pretending not to see themost of the citizens with whom she shares the street.  She only allows hergaze to be met by other members of Thesden's nobility.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tall nobleman is walking here, his servants trailing behind.
Mobiles.Description: He walks with a studied poise, head facing foreward, each step fallingfirmly.  The peasantry in the crowd parts before him, avoiding his gaze andstaring at their feet.  His hand occasionally taps the hilt of the swordhanging from his belt, as if to remind himself that it is there.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A plump merchant deftly weaves his way through the crowd.
Mobiles.Description: He wears a long velvet cloak, wrapped over his expensive silk clothes ofthe latest fashion.  He looks like an easy target, but you notice a certainwariness in his step, and a surprising dexterity of movement for his weight.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aa man dressed in black creeps along in the shadows.``
Mobiles.Description: A nondescript man in clothing unexceptional in every way, he blends intothe Thesden crowds.  He doesn't seem to mind being overlooked, and will,seemingly happy, stand there for hours while others converse.  Anyone whowatches him carefully will note that while his hands seem graceful enough,he seems to have a propensity to bump into people.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sorrowful man stands on the scaffold, awaiting his fate.
Mobiles.Description: He stands quietly, waiting for a chance to speak his last words.  His jawis set, and he stands proudly, only in his eyes can you see a hint of fear,sadness, and rage.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A squire is running errands for his lord here.
Mobiles.Description: A boy of probably no more than fifteen, this squire is participating inone of his less exciting tasks as squire for a noble knight.  His clothesare plain, but well-made and he wears the colors and coat of arms of hismaster's royal family.  His face shows a determination and his physique isbeginning to show the benefits of a rigorous lifestyle under the guidance ofa knight of the crown.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A merchant from distant lands is standing here.
Mobiles.Description: You smell a vague scent of salty sea air mixed with a faint trace ofspices as he passes by you, giving you no more than a quick, disintrestedglance.  He wears white cotton robes, and a thick, square black beard.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An angry looking bodyguard is watching out for trouble here.
Mobiles.Description: You suspect he has a lot of experience being a thug.  He puffs his chestout as he moves down the street, looking around him with a sneer on hismouth and a hand on his club.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A ship's captain is enjoying some time walking on dry land.
Mobiles.Description: The captain's face is worn by years of sea air, ragged but not wrinkled,and covered in a thin greying beard.  He moves with a quiet grace despitehis size, dodging swiftly through the crowds filling the streets.  Othersailors seem to avoid his eyes, hanging their heads and walking quicklypast.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The warden is here, watching the cells carefully.
A foreigner dressed in red robes walks by in bare feet.
A serious young man in black stares at you with a look of damnation and hope.
Mobiles.Description: Wearing the unmistakable garb of the Church, black woolens with thesilver triskelion hanging from his neck on a silver chain.  He is walks thestreets, looking for people to listen to the word, and to hear the storiesof the martyrs.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A scarred dwarven bodyguard watches for danger to his employer.
Mobiles.Description: This dwarf is all about business, and his business is the protection ofhis client.  Short, but sturdy, the bodyguard bears the scars of a hardlifetime of conflict.  Probably a former soldier or mercenary, he has founda new life in the employ of Thesden's upper crust.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A Thesden guard patrols the streets here.
Mobiles.Description: Eagerness shines on the face of this young guard.  Many things shine,actually, from the polished sword hilt to the eyelets on the boots.  Thisguard's uniform has been carefully pressed and cleaned.  Too new to bejaded, but too conscientious to be anything but careful, this young guardscans everything constantly, trying to keep the peace to the best of theirability.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A grey-haired man is standing here, examining his nails.
Mobiles.Description: He wears faded plain brown leather, and seems entirely relaxed even inthe most dangerous of neighborhoods.  Looking more closely, you noticeseveral sharp daggers stored in his belt, boots and perhaps elsewhere.  Youalso note that most of the locals seem to be staying far clear of him.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA tall knight wearing heavy plate armor is here.``
Mobiles.Description: He moves with surprising grace in the heavy armor, never showing any signof weariness.  He is still not old enough to sit among the elders of theorder, though he is surely a formidable warrior.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A woman is standing here, leaning on a wooden staff.
Mobiles.Description: She appears to be lost in thought, her brow furrowed and her gazedirected into the sky just above the buildings.  A small, crescent shapedmark on her shirt indicates that she is a member of the mages guild.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The executioner is here, waiting to enact justice.
The battered rather worn out practice golem is here, providing a moving target for magics.
`iBefore you stands Zeryn, the master of the crescent moon mage guild.``
Mobiles.Description: Having been ordained by the High Priest of Thesden, this mage's devotionto the church has been rewarded with the honor of protecting the churchagainst the unrighteous and instructing the young in proper reverance.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The master looks furious with you for disturbing his work.
Mobiles.Description: As is apparent from the silver that gilds his head, Ylris is an olderelf, perhaps one of the eldest in Thesden.  His dark eyes, often distantwith thought, have something of a sadness to them, particularly when helooks at the tapestry in his office.  Elegant pointed ears poke through thehair that needs a combing, and his robe show signs of former elegance worn abit too long, and now just a bit shabby from neglect.  Rumor has it that themaster, known for being more interested in magical theory than use,teleported himself out of Ilewyen one day and just never noticed that he hadchanged location.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The keeper of the supply shop is here, waiting for you to purchase something.
`aa midnight black raven is perched nearby here.``
Mobiles.Description: Certainly no ordinary bird, there is a mischievous glitter in its coldblack eyes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aa sleek black cat moves quietly through the shadows.``
Mobiles.Description: The cat moves gracefully, dipping in and out of the shadows.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `ba small fire drake circles in the air above your head.``
Mobiles.Description: No larger than a cat, this miniature dragon is covered in red scales.  Itoccasionally stops flying an rests briefly on the ground, waiting for a signof some useful direction to travel.  It looks up at you occasionally, andalmost seems to be grinning.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `ga small frost drake circles above your head here.``
Mobiles.Description: This small dragon is no larger than a cat.  It is covered in blue scales,and flies on bat-like wings.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `ca nasty, hunched little homonculus creeps along behind its master.``
Mobiles.Description: The creature's flesh is green and rubbery, and it moves quickly on itsclawed little feet.  The homonculus is wrought by dark magic, created as aservant for powerful wizards.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oIsaac, the most holy of clerics, tends to his cathedral.``
Mobiles.Description: He wears plain brown robes, no decorations save a simple woodentriskelion pendant.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The high priest looks up from a book as you enter.
Mobiles.Description: The high priest stands thoughtfully by the book-shelf in his crampedoffice.  You can read no emotion on his face, lost in the shadows of theblue-black hood of his robes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A ghostly presence howls and floats toward you.
Mobiles.Description: Just a thin, wispy grey outline is all that remains of the body of thispoor soul.  Trapped here for an enternity after being offered at the altarabove.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The preacher stands beside the podium, face as expressionless as stone.
Mobiles.Description: The preacher stands here in his simple black woolens.  He looks solemnlyout at the pews, as he waits for worshipers to gather for his next sermon...Gossip says he has a special one planned on murder.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `jVanya, the ranger guildmaster, stands before you.``
Mobiles.Description: Vanya is a beautiful human woman with long brown hair and a slenderfigure.  She is well-known throughout these lands as a fierce protector ofthe woods and all who would live within its borders.  She has risen upthrough the ranks of the rangers to lead them, and rightfully so, despiteher relatively young age.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An almost worn out practice dummy is here.
`oSir Vedros, the warrior guildmaster, stands here proudly.``
Mobiles.Description: Sir Vedros stands and walks with all the grace of a man in his sixties,but with the energy and strength of a man half that age.  Cold blue eyesstare at you compassionately, watching your moves, but not judging you.Clearly, he is a man who wants to pass on his knowledge.  He stands a bitover six feet tall and has straight brown shoulder-length hair and a longmustache to match.  Vedros was a soldier in King Athanmere's Argent army whodistinguished himself in combat, eventually rising through the ranks to leadthe King's personal bodyguards.  Sworn to defend his King to the death,Vedros now serves the crown as a guildmaster and teacher of young warriors.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A huge brown bear growls as you step into her home.
`aIvan one-eye is here, he could probably teach you a thing or two.``
Mobiles.Description: Still slim and fit looking, Ivan shows few signs of his age other thanthe silken patch that covers one eye, and the streaks of silver that tracethrough his hair.  Ivan is neither noble nor particularly gracious inappearance or manner, but rather the kind of guy that you would lose easilyin a crowd.  This, in all likelihood, has stood this premier thief in goodstead throughout his long and colorful career.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A skinny, mole-ish man works behind the bar here.
Mobiles.Description: You aren't exactly sure how this frail man has survived, with hisbusiness and life intact, in such a rough part of town.  His hair is stringyand thin and hangs down over his pointy pock-marked rodent face.  He grinsat you, waiting for an order.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe bards' guildmaster, Aldera, practices a tune.``
Mobiles.Description: In her youth, the bard Aldera was known throughout the Realm for heradventuring prowess.  She was among the first to ropen communications withthe distant Keep of Krathen, some say in order to incorporate the oddwhistling music of the Krathe into her repertoire.  Now, she has happilyretired from adventuring, and, as she will tell anyone who asks, doing asall bards should dream of doing: sitting on her duff dispensing her opinionas if it was priceless to the younger generation.  As she will readilyadmit, Aldera is more than happy to enjoy a peaceful life, with a roof overher head, plenty of good food, and someone to pick up after her.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A tiny minnow swims happily through the muck here.
`aThe courier is here, greedily counting the jewels inside the package.``
Mobiles.Description: `aHaving worked his way up from beggar, to pickpocket, and finally tofavored courier.  Delivering unmarked packages to shady individuals all overThesden for Pook of the Hand, the undisputed lord of the dark side of`aThesden, and perhaps even more than that.  But one day the courier'scuriousity got the better of him and he opened a package that he wassupposed to deliver to Pook...  Inside he found several rubies, emeralds and`adiamonds.  Being a thief and all, he decided to keep this fortune,foolhardily risking the wrath of Pook.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: Pook reclines in an armchair here, assured that nobody would dare to attack him.
Mobiles.Description: `aPook is known to the citizens and nobles of Thesden as 'Pook thebenevolent' handing out money to the poor, and donating money to the farmersof the Eastern Prairie.  Of course, being the bastard son of FerathAthanmere himself, nothing less is to be expected.  `aAt thirteen years ofage Pook swore he would one day rule Thesden, though he later realized thathe would not become king because he is not a 'true' son of the Athanmereline.  One day when he was wandering the streets of the city he met a manthat later would become his best friend.  Spink, as he was named, wasdeformed and cross-eyed, but he had a winning personality.  Pook immideatlytook a liking to the ugly little man.  As it turned out, Spink was initiallytrying to get a noble connection inside the Castle Dunlace.  See, Spink wasactually one of the best thieves in all of Thesden, if not the best.  InPook he saw great potential for the dark arts.  Over the years he took Pookwith him on little quests, 'pranks' as he called them.  Stealing from therich and giving to the poor, he said, of course he was not very picky aboutthe last part of that sentence.  Without Pook realizing it, he was taught tobe the perfect thief, with all the treats that belong, lockpicking,pickpocketing, sneaking and spying.  At the age of seventeen, Pook hadaccess to the Royal Treasure Chamber thanks to his skills with a lock pick.What Spink had recognized in Pook was not only charisma and leader skillsbut also a far above average intelligence.  Pook soon understood what kindof person Spink was, a thief and a murderer.  But he found that he likedthat way of life and he was soon accepted into '`hThe Hand`a', the thief andassassin guild of Thesden.  Years passed and Pook was soon only second toIvan.  His genius in the arts of larceny and assassination in fact surpassedeven Ivan's.  When he was nineteen years of age he challenged Ivan for theleadership of '`hThe Hand`a'.  It was a duel of skill and dexterity but Pookleft the duel as the leader of the guild, and from that day on, Ivan wouldbe known as Ivan One-eye.  And though Pook rules the underworld of Thesden,he keeps the facade of a nobleman.  Living in a mansion that is onlyoutshined by Harris's.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Ransak the Fist is towering above you, always ready to defend its master.
Mobiles.Description: `aAfter a close encounter with one of Jericka's, the assassin guild master,dagger, Pook decided that he needed an ever-watching bodyguard.  For even aMaster Thief can not be awake all the time.  He talked to an old aquiantanceof his, Anouen Forundal, about this and was soon provided with a solution, agolem.  Anouen asked Pook to bring him fresh corpses of Sidhe and Vro'athas the components of the flesh golem.  Pook had no problem with getting thecorpses.  Anouen built a golem with the parts from the Vro'ath corpses andcovered his creation with a skin of Sidhe hide.  Combining the strengths ofthe Vro'ath and the magical abilities of the Sidhe skin, Anouen had createdan almost indestructable Juggernaut.  The only problem was that the creaturehad no soul and no will to obey anyone.  Anouen solved this by sacrificing adozen`k Runes of Convergence`a to the demon lord Iverath, and asked if thedemon could inbue Anouen's creation with the soul of a devil.  Iverathaccepted the offering and brought the flesh golem to life.`aThe golem was named Ransak and was clothed in heavy chain coif and mail tohide its hideous features.  Only two great tusks and the devil-red eyes canbe seen from under the coif as it watches your every move.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A warhorse stands here proudly, head held high.
Mobiles.Description: This graceful, spirited warhorse is still young enough to have spring inits step and a propensity to frolic when it thinks no one is looking.  Builtfor strength and shod in iron, this beast can switch gears on the smallestsignal from its master or mistress.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A short, slim man is stacking boxes of cigars on the counter here.
Lord Istian glares at you as you pass, looking generally perturbed.
Mobiles.Description: Upon his shirt is woven the silvery body of a dragon, the symbol of hisfamily, one of the wealthiest in Thesden.  He stands quite tall, over sixfeet, with a inky black thin beard and cropped black hair.  His brow isfurrowed with concern, over what you can only guess.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A pale, broad shouldered man is staring intently at a ship blueprint.
`jAn elven hunter looks strangely out of place in Thesden.``
A town watchman guards the street vigilantly here.
Mobiles.Description: Thesden, being a city of great magnificence and wealth, requires theconstant attention of a trained militia.  The town guard is made up ofable-bodied men and women who live in and around town, and who volunteertheir services for the mutual protection of their homes and businesses.  Thetown guard are not soldiers by trade, but have received combat training fromthe Argent Lance instructors.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A short middle aged woman stands behind the bar, serving drinks.
Mobiles.Description: Laisa is a harsh woman, taking nothing from the brash sailors whopatronize her establisment.  Her greying black hair is pulled back tight,and her eyes are narrow and alert as she looks about the room for anyone outof line.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A thin, scarred man looks about him in fear.
Mobiles.Description: This mouse like man cluthes a silvery amulet to him closely, lookingabout nervously.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A Thesden guard has been assigned to keep the peace between the clans here.
Mobiles.Description: Having been assigned to this post by the Mayor of Thesden, this guardstands vigilantly here to make sure that no clans come to blows within theconfines of this enclosure.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA child is here, innocently sucking on a lollipop.``
Mobiles.Description: `hInnocent blue eyes looks at you curiously from under a mop of blondehair.  Not saying a word he stuffs his mouth with candy that he can somehowafford.  He smiles at you with all his face as you walk away.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A Thesden guard patrols the streets here.
Mobiles.Description: This guard looks fit and alert, looking about carefully for suspiciousactivity.  A little silver touches the hair of this guard, and a few crowsfeet track at the the corners of the eyes of this guard.  Experience hastoughened this guard and increased his effectiveness.  Somewhere along theway, he has picked up a fondness for devil's weed.  A well-honed blade restseasily in his hand.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A straw and wood mannequin waits for students to practice combat on it.
A mannequin of straw and wood has been erected here to practice the arts of combat on.
A golem made of straw has been erected by the eastern wall on which clerics can practice the arts of self defense.
A mannequin of straw and wood has been erected here to practice the arts of thievery on.
Mobiles.Description: A crude dummy, of straw and wood, has been erected here to practice thefine arts of thievery on.  Someone has painted a Thesden guard uniform onit, and the paint is flaking slightly.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fA young girl sits in the ledge, defiantly puffing on her pipe as she meets your eyes.``
Mobiles.Description: Her face and bare upper arms are bruised and scratched from fighting.Fighting over the leadership of the 'The Rats', a network that spans allover Thesden, consisting of children acting as spies for 'The Hand'.  Totoughen her appearance she has aquired a pipe to bite down on.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe local sawbones 'Doctor' Giggles invites you over to the examination table.``
Mobiles.Description: Yup, he has that look.  You know, that 'mad scientist' look.  Licking hisscalpel, he looks you up and down, as if to decide where to start cuttingfirst.  His apron is a rubbery red leather, and you have no misconceptionsof why it is of that particular color.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fA drunk noble woman lies in a heap on the bed, snoring loudly.``
Mobiles.Description: How...  Lovely..  This snoring, drooling and not to mention middle-agedwoman lies sprawled on a canopy bed here.  Tresses of sweaty blonde haircovers her face and neck, fluttering slightly as she snores.  A low-cutdress made of pink silk reveals way too much saggy skin for your liking, butyou were just here to rob her anyways, right?

Mobiles.LongDescription: (no long description)
A Thesden guard is here, protecting the innocent and jailing people like you.
Mobiles.Description: This guard looks fit and alert, looking about carefully for suspiciousactivity.  A little silver touches the hair of this guard, and a few crowsfeet track at the the corners of the eyes of this guard.  Experience hastoughened this guard and increased his effectiveness.  Somewhere along theway, he has picked up a fondness for devil's weed.  A well-honed blade restseasily in his hand.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A bum lies comfortably in a heap of something..not clean.
Mobiles.Description: He looks kind of filthy, he smells it too.  Fighting with the rats, dogsand alley cats of Thesden for every meal, you see bite and scratch marks onhis face and arms.  He is missing most of the hair of his head, that wouldbe much needed on cold nights.  He burps and farts uncontrollably, what acharming fellow.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An aging, burly man with thinning hair offers you a room.
Mobiles.Description: A burly, aging man, Aphrun exemplifies an Innkeeper.  His eyes, how theytwinkle!  His dimples, how merry!  His cheeks are like roses, and his noselike a (rather suspect) cherry!  His droll little mouth is drawn up like abow, and the beard on his chin is as white as snow.  A jolly old man, he'squick to laugh, and when he does, his little round belly shakes, like a bowlfull of jelly.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A bank robber is here, making for the town gates with a big bag of `kgold!``
A skeletal corpse rises and moves slowly towards you.
Mobiles.Description: The body is dressed in the tattered rags of a captain's uniform, it opensits mouth and howls silently.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A graceful young woman waits behind the counter here.
The solemn figure before you compels even the most devilish to stand back in holy awe.
A bank robber is here, trying to get out of town with a big bag of loot!
`hA grey and white pigeon is stupidly pecking the empty roof.``
Mobiles.Description: Not one of the smartest animals around. Flap and peck, all day long.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA grey and white pigeon is stupidly pecking the empty roof.``
Mobiles.Description: Not one of the smartest animals around. Flap and peck, all day long.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA grey and white pigeon is stupidly pecking the empty roof.``
Mobiles.Description: Not one of the smartest animals around. Flap and peck, all day long.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA grey and white pigeon is stupidly pecking the empty roof.``
Mobiles.Description: Not one of the smartest animals around. Flap and peck, all day long.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA monk sits on the bed, weary from his travels.``
Mobiles.Description: `hThis monk recently arrived to Thesden from the hidden village ofKaruasandru, where the greatest of martial artists reside.  Little is knownof why the monks recently decided to leave their peaceful mountain village.Rumors have that they were driven out, but given the nature of these monks,you find that to be highly unlikely.  The man before you is a little on thesmall side, with a lean build, he actually looks quite harmless... ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA tall monk is standing here, smoking some`c herbs`h.``
Mobiles.Description: `dSeemingly relaxed, this monk is leaning against a wall, smoking a pipethat by the smell of it is stuffed with blue weed.  He smiles kindly as youtip your hat in his direction.  He is very tall for a human, and his broadshoulders make him seem even bigger.  As he shifts you notice a certaingrace in his movements, there is no doubt that this man is well-versed inthe fighting arts.  `` `dLike many other monks, this one arrived recently,having travelled from a far off mountain village called Karuasandru.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A mouse runs by, darting into crevices in the city streets.
A little girl is here, on her way to school.
A teenaged girl walks by, a dreamy faroff look on her face.
Mobiles.Description: Clearly glad to finally have come of age, this girl glances shyly away asshe notices you observing her.  Skinny and maybe a bit gawky, she gigglesnervously and stuffs a crumpled up piece of paper in her pocket as youwatch.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A man stands behind a stall here, offering tickets to the crowd.
`dA tiny hummingbird flits about here, sipping pollen from flowers.``
A grimy earthworm ruts about in the soil here.
`oA snowcapped izida bird roosts on a tiny wooden pole here.``
An animal feeder walks along here, carrying a sack of grain and meat.
`cAn alligator thrashes about in the depths here, awaiting his next meal.``
`aA cute baby seal barks up at you from inside a trough of water.``
A gaunt man clad in a rubbery black outfit manages the animals here.
`iA red-tailed Raiuk fish lounges about in the cool water here.``
`oA flat albino ray swims in the shadows here.``
A crisp white watergull perches above the pool here, searching for tidbits.
A patron of the zoo wanders about, examining the animals within.
A grimy mud salamander pulls itself out of a pool of filth here.
`dA wily chimpanzee swings through branches here.``
A large gorilla snarls at you as you approach him.
A baboon smiles at you happily, and then throws dirt in your face.
A grey-striped brown tiger curls itself around something in the grass.
A yellow cougar raises an eyebrow at you and then settles back down.
`cA crocodile raises a thin snout out of the bog and stares at you.``
`jA thin green snake hangs down from a black willow tree.``
`aA thick-bodied bog snake slithers through the muck here.``
`eA pit lizard lumbers about the room, snapping at air.``
Mobiles.Description: A gigantic flat head frames two large nasal pits and three small gleamingred eyes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A young girl sucks on a lollipop as she looks at the animals.
Mobiles.Description: This little girl is immaculately dressed in a little white dress with amatching hat with ribbons, all completely spotless.  Her hair has beencarefully combed into pigtails, and all in all, she's an adorable andastonishingly well behaved child.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A teenage girl sleeps quietly here under the trees.
Mobiles.Description: A sweet-faced young girl, this babysitter was hired to watch the youngchild of a Thesden noble.  However, exhausted from a party the night before(where that really cute guy talked to her!)  , she dozed off and her chargehas wandered away.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA camel is here, uh oh! It's got a scud missile strapped between the humps!``
`lGodfrey, the lord of the templars, waits to train aspiring paladins.``
Mobiles.Description: Tall and imposing, his beard and hair turned to silver, the Lord of theTemplars is still fit and ready for duty, should the forces of good requirethis hero.  While his position requires him to assume the duties of abureaucrat, Lord Godfrey is always willing to put away his papers, pick uphis lance, and aid a younger paladin.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A battered and almost destroyed dummy awaits the next round of pummeling.
(no long description)
A translucent Sidhe mage grins at you mischievously as he leans on his wooden staff.
The famous bard, Xorke, stands here playing his lute and singing of a distant lands.

Mobiles.ShortDescription: An acolyte of the order of Xork
Mobiles.LongDescription: An acolyte of the Xorkian order stands here preaching about the lighter sides of life.
Mobiles.Description: Dressed in a scarlet robe wearing a silver 'X' from her neck, an acolyte of Xorksmiles upon you and tells you that everyone needs a little humor in their livesevery day that you walk upon the earth.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oCyril, `hThe rat-collector is searching for rats.``
Mobiles.Description: Cyril is a tall skinny man with a long nose and a slender face.  Hisshifty eyes appear placed too close together and dart from one place toanother, as though always on the lookout for something.  He is dressed theclothes of a travelling merchant, only he peddles no wares.  Cyril is arat-collector by trade and he's always looking for some part-time help.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA travelling warrior`` is here.
Mobiles.Description: `aAt first glance, all that can be seen is a glimmer.  Upon taking asecond look, you see that the light grey eyes of this man are wise but notold.  The silvery hair reflects back even the slightest light that itcatches.  Pure steel is what comes to mind, combined with the strong bodyand its silvery accoutrements, when considering this opponent.  While veryserious, there are laugh lines upon the face of this man.  He is one to helpa friend without being asked, and can be the worst of enemies to those thatdare.  Be sure to decide which of these you wish to be.  Wisdom comes to allin time, but steeliness and cunning are inborn traits--obviously given tothis man at birth.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aAzaran stands before the altar, performing an ancient ritual.``
`gBuilder Bob`` stands here, eager to tell you all about building.
Mobiles.Description: He looks like a nice guy, and if you are too lazy to read the sign on the wallask him a question about`k building``.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An old gnome looks up at you through his spectacles.
Mobiles.Description: Tim the tinkerer is a bespectacled old gnome with an inquizitive natureand an infectious smile.  He stands only a bit taller than a dwarf, but he'smuch more slender.  He looks up at you over his little glasses, which reston his long nose and asks if he can be of assistance.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA mad monkey is here, acting like a damn fool and raising havoc.``
A zookeeper is here
`jDervin, the retired ranger, sells good for the common good.``
(no long description)
A girl has been bitten by the bog snake and needs some help.
`gTwo feet are taking up the better part of the street, as you stare up in amazement you see the terrible`l Stay-Puft`o Marshmallow`l Man!``
`oA ghost of `aH`ia`al`il`ao`iw`ae`ie`an `oPast`a floats here ominously.``
Mobiles.Description: This ghost only comes around once a year.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Marguerite is here, selling gear to neophytes in need.
A heavy set middle aged man, hands folded across his lap, sits here in repose.
Mobiles.Description: In keeping with the fact that he often looks asleep even when he isawake, Dexton is a peaceful soul, content in his home and family.  He'snever felt a call to adventure, nor to fight.  The only calls it looks likehe's answered are those to the dinner table, and to take a nap.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A wandering minstrel, clad in gaudy finery, stands here entertaining passersby.
Mobiles.Description: This young man smiles at you with eyes too wide and guileless to be trulyso.  His hair is cut short, and curls around an open, friendly face, ratherlike that of puppy.  As if to compensate for his appearance, Baxan's outfitis outlandish to an extreme.  He wears a tunic that is a rainbow ofbrilliant color, tie-dyed.  His leggings are not only cross-gartered withsilvery laces, but cut out shapes, round circles of black, and golden starscomplete the garish outfit.  A worn, polished lyre hangs over a shoulder,safely strapped (with orange and mauve straps!)  So as not to get in the wayof any acrobatic performances.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A duck waddles around contentedly in the grass.
A chipmunk, cheeks bulging with nuts, forages for winter storage.
A young woman stands here, gazing into space under the shade of her parasol.
Mobiles.Description: The deep creases around her eyes give her the appearance of being much olderthan she actually is.  She holds her head resolutely, as if bound by some dutyto remain proud and brazen, though she has obviously been struck bysome immense tragedy.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oA dove bids you welcome into this tranquil garden with soft coos.``
A wizened old man sits on the bench, engrossed in a book.
Mobiles.Description: Aged wrinkled hands and white hair aside, the brightness of Old Man Torun'seyes dissuade you from thinking that you are looking at a feeble old man.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A half-elven gardener is here, meticulously tending to the gardens.
A templar knight proudly stands here guarding the church from unrighteousness.
An elderly Vro'ath sits behind an oak table, examining an ancient tome.
Mobiles.Description: Hin'Grak is the has-been lore-master of the Varruk army for nearly a century, andit is he who searches out the ancient relics and sacred artifacts for dispersalinto the clan's ranks.  As he sees you enter, he closes the ancient tome and standsup from the table, realizing what you have come here for.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Zachari, the ancient Syvin scholar, bids you welcome into his shop.
Mobiles.Description: Zachari, an ancient Syvin, with long silver hair has been harvsting tools, weaponsand armor for close to a century.  Renowned for his skills as a ranger, it was anatural progression for him from a Protector of the Forests to guide and outfitterof the latest generation of Greenwood members as his mastery of Syvin lore andcraft are unparalleled.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A non-descript human named, Schmo, stands here with a blank look on his face.
`gA nervous sidhe greedily hugs his baubles here.``
`bA tired and emaciated wretch of a man is here, working faster than humanly possible.``
Mobiles.Description: `bAfter the great clan wars of the 1654, Clive was dispelled from theclan after he caused the downfall of Parlous.  Several years later, afterthe reinstiution of Parlous, a mage charmed Clive, and has now forced him torepay his trasgressions by serving the clan till his death comes.  Andperhaps after that as well.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: Gobbler the Artificer bids you welcome into his shop.
Mobiles.Description: Here sits the eternal mage of the`o Elder``, Magis.  He spends his days creating andduplicating equipment for his beloved clan`g Twilight``.  The symbol of`n Twilight`` isetched upon his right hand, the symbol of the`b Caedes`` upon his left.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A man on a wooden leg named, Stimpy, smiles at you here.
A wide, jolly man by the name of Barney, welcomes you to his shop.
A man with a peg leg and eye-patch stands here holding a lot of booty.
A drifter, wrapped in a leather cloak, wanders the streets.
Mobiles.Description: The drifter wears a hooded cloak with the hood hanging loose behind herback.  She has long brown hair and eyes that sparkle as she scans the crowdsaround her.  Nobody pays her much mind and she goes about her business as aforeigner, passing through Thesden en route to destinations unknown.  As shewalks, her cape swings open, giving you a good look at an arsenal of bladeshanging from her belt.  Perhaps she is an assassin for hire, or perhaps justan adventurer who is just in town for the day.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA sneaky-looking Sidhe buzzes around the shop trailing wisps of smoke.``
Mobiles.Description: Roscoe is a short plump Sidhe who reeks of cheap cigars.  He buzzes around theroom on wings that look far too tiny to support his considerable weight.  It'sclear that Roscoe has not made his living performing physical labor.  As hesees you his lip curls back into a grin so big it almost looks like a sneer.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A HUGE rat skulks about in the shadows.
Mobiles.Description: This small, beady-eyed wonder sure looks like a rat.  Grey fur, quiveringwhiskerings, naked pink tail, and a predilection for cheese, this iscertainly a rat.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gSkullmaster`` is here.``
`iA leashed devil stands here snarling its owner.``
`mMissus Primple`f, the stand-in executioner stands-in here, wielding some enourmous nail-clippers.``
Mobiles.Description: `hWow, what a hottie, bot that nail-clipper looks mighty dangerous, charm her or go away!``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `o(Invis) `aMild the `cRanger `ais here, `kAFKing `ain the `cprairie `aas usual.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA strange looking bitter ranger is sitting here, staring blankly at anopen prairie.  He seems to be missing a hand and you notice the fact that heis invisible and not camoed.  If nothing else you notice this is a verystupid ranger.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sinewy man lurks here, eyeing you suspiciously.
Mobiles.Description: Known all throughout Thesden for his amazing skills of tracking criminalsdown, Birger is regularly employed by the town guard.  He works for cheap,because he truly enjoys his profession.  His face and arms are covered inoutlandish, glowing tattoos, rumors have it that they are inbued withmagical properties, allowing him to see beyond normal human sight and givinghim an acute sense of smell.  Judging from his brutish apperance, though,you suspect that a forefather of his was an orc, or worse.  His hair isgreen and browning, if that is his natural hair color you dare not guess, itmight as well be dirt and moss.  His nose bulges out of his face like as ifhe was hit really hard in the back of the head as a child.  The eyes aresmall sit far apart, probably to enable him to see past the warty monster ofa nose.  His sinewy frame is held up by a crooked back which he seems tohang from like a scarecrow.  Dragging his feet along as he shuffles alongCumberland Avenue his darting eyes suspiciously search the streets for shadyindividuals.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThorasan`` is lurking in the shadows here.``
Mobiles.Description: `aA tall figure lurks around you, appearing slightly from the shadows.  Itappears to be one with the surroundings and the only thing clear are thepiercing silver eyes darting quickly around the area.  He moves quickly anddeliberately and his hooded grey cloak surrounds him and seems inpenetrable.You lose sight of the figure and think you have seen a ghost and then youfeel ever so lighter.  As you smile and tell yourself everything is fine younotice something......WHERE IS MY GOLD.....ITS GONE!!!!``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oThe `nK`ge`ne`gp`ne`gr `ostands here waiting patiently.``
Mobiles.Description: `hA smiling woman looks down at you, the `nK`ge`ne`gp`ne`gr `oof the`nS`gt`na`gr`ns```h, sent down from the sky to help and protect clan`n*`g*`n*`oTwilight`n*`g*`n* `hin any way she possibly could.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA `nbeautiful`g water nymph stands here, waiting to serve you.``
A blinding light and an echoing roar mark this silver dragon's presence.
Mobiles.Description: Humongous mercury scales overlap in a crisscross jigsaw, sending waves oflight sparkling down this dragon's back every time a muscle ripples underneathher skin.  Thin, intelligent eyes assess you calmly as the dragon tenses,ready for whatever situation you plan on presenting her with.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA black `fp`aa`fn`at`fh`ae`fr`a cub stealthily stalks its prey.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe black `fp`aa`fn`at`fh`ae`fr `auses its keen senses and instinct to gain advantage on its unsuspecting prey.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: Pescado the fisherman stares at the sea, dreaming of huge fish.
Mobiles.Description: Pescado is an old man.  His wrinkled skin is leathery from thousands ofhours in the sun.  His face is tan and his eyes possess a calm longing as hestares out at the waves.  It is said that Pescado was a champion fishermanlong ago, but has retired.  Now he simply dreams of the legendary fish thatescaped his hook.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA kalian playing with a bowl of `bblood`a licks the excess off her fingers.``
Your first love walks around here, the knife is still protruding from the spine. Good.
`iA team of gnomish engineers have completed their lamp!``
Mobiles.Description: `iThis team of gnomish engineers are a special team dispatched ```ifrom the great `kD`du`ki`dw`ke`dl`k'`ds `kC`do`kn`ds`kt`dr`ku`dc`kt`di`ko`dn `kS`di`kt`de `ito put up a lamp.```iHaving completed their task, they are resting here before ```igoing back to the work site.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A test shopkeeper
An aged woman with half-closed eyes smiles at you strangely.
Mobiles.Description: Zannah's past is a mystery, she has worked here in Thesden as long asanyone can remember.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA kalian playing with a bowl of `bblood`a licks the excess off her fingers.``
`aA `bDeranged `jEa`mst`je`mr `kB`hu`knn`hy `kRabbit``
`mG`oeorge`h, the `mr`oabbit`h, twitches his whiskers and looks at you with beady little eyes.``
Mobiles.Description: `hUpon closer inspection of `mG`oeorge`h, he is exactly what he appearsto be at first glance -- an oversized, talking, `mpurple`h and `owhite`hstuffed rabbit.  Some amazing magic is surely at work here to make thisgigantic child's toy move and speak as if it were alive!  ``

Rooms.RoomDescription: This square marks the intersection of Cumberland Avenue (east/west) andCrowland Street (North/South).  At the center stands a withered old elmtree, dead branches and names of a hundred sweethearts carved into itstrunk.  Two deep ruts run from the east side to the south side, showing thepath of the wagons from east Thesden to the docks to the south.

This quiet little street is home to a number of slightly run-down homesand apartments.  There is quite a bit of commotion to the south in Elmsquare, to the north, however, only a few people walk unhurriedly.

You walk along a quiet back street away from the din of the main squares.Ramshackle houses stand along the road, only some of which appear to beoccupied.  Besides the fact that the street is unpaved and covered in dirt,it appears surprisingly well kept, raked and free of trash.

The roads end in a short wooden pier which projects out over the murkywaters of the Severn River.  The pier has a rotted wooden fence, which youcould easily jump over and dive down into the river, though the stench makesyou think that might not be a great idea.

You are above the dark, swirling waters of the Severn River.  You coulddive under the murky waters, though the vague stench of sewage makes youthink you might regret it.  The river flows from the north, through a rustedgrate at the bottom of the city wall.

You are swimming in the foul waters of the Severn River.  The waters aremurky and dark, you find it quite difficult to see anything.  The swirlingwaters carry some small fish, and much else not nearly so harmless.

This street leads from the Thesden docks to the south to Elm square justto the north.  A thick layer of dust and gravel coat the ground, clouds ofdust occasionally rising as a merchant wagon moves by quickly.  Grim-facedpeasants mix with the dock workers and merchants, all carefully avoiding eyecontact.

Increasing amounts of mud sticks to your boots as you walk along thisroad, winding past merchants headed to the docks and poor locals looking fora coin.  A small sign outside a building to the east reads, `d'Midnight'sSmoke Shop'`e.

The smell of salt water and old fish drifts through the air from thedocks not far off to the south.  Merchants wagons create clouds of dust inthe air as they roll past to load cargo from the ships and bring it back tothe center of town.

The smell of sea air is quite strong this close to the docks to thesouth, getting milder to the north.  A steady flow of merchants, wagons, andburly guards move along to and from the docks carrying goods back to themain part of town.

A steady breeze rolls in off the bay, carrying with it salty air and thesmell of fish.  Wide sailed sloops and smaller ships can be seen floatingout in the bay, heading out to sea or coming into port.  Dock Streetcontinues to the east and west, Crowland Street leads off to the north.

Small waves, cresting with the slightest white froth, lap at the base ofthe long wooden piers where ships of all sizes are docked.  The smell ofsalt and sea air is strong here, carried on a light breeze.  Dock streetmeets Crowland just to the west.

Small waves, cresting with the slightest white froth, lap at the base ofthe long wooden piers where ships of all sizes are docked.  The smell ofsalt and sea air is strong here, carried on a light breeze.

Small waves, cresting with the slightest white froth, lap at the base ofthe long wooden piers where ships of all sizes are docked.  The smell ofsalt and sea air is strong here, carried on a light breeze.  The street endsin rotten wooden fence on a platform which overlooks the Severn Riveremptying into the bay.

The salty air of the sea leaves your throat feeling horribly dry, luckily`d'The Rusty Nail Tavern'`l is just to the north.  The docks continue to thewest, to the east meeting up with merchants coming off Crowland street.  Along wooden pier runs off to the south.

A light breeze blows steadily, carrying the scents of the sea from thebay across the ships floating by the wooden docks.  Fewer ships are dockedon this west end of the street, even fewer further west.  Small waves rollin from the bay, causing the ships to rise and fall steadily.  A neatlypainted sign above a building to the north reads `dAsrac's Ships.  ``

The docks end here, only a short beach of gravel and sand to the south.Gulls circle above here, staring down into the water looking for a likelyfish or crab to eat.  The docks can be seen off to the east, and a narrow,dark street to the north.

Buildings, wood rotted and partially collapsed, filled with far too manypeople or none at all, line this narrow street.  No one meets your eyes,most concentrate solely on where their feet are headed and on the locationof their meagre purses.  You can hear the sound of waves crashing just tothe south.

The houses on this narrow street are in poor shape, overcrowded orfalling down or both.  Trash rolls along with small clouds of dust in thebreeze, twirling around the feet of grim-faced locals walking by.

A narrow residential street, decrepit homes along Falstaff cower withcurtains drawn along the sides.  Trash lies discarded randomly over the dirtstreet, blowing around with the breeze.  The few people in the street movequickly, avoiding eye-contact.

This is clearly no one of the wealthier sections of Thesden, thebuildings mostly look like they don't have long left in this world and thelocals don't look much better off.  You can see the towers of the west gatejust to the north.

The thick wooden gates of Thesden are to the west, flanked by two tallrounded towers.  Only a few travelers or merchants occasionally come throughthe gates, heading quickly to the east side of town along Cumberland.  Anarrow, dark street crosses here, heading off to the north and south.

This narrow street is almost empty, most of the houses are abandoned orhave their curtains drawn.  To the south, the twin towers of the West Gatecan be seen, rising above the city walls.  To the north, the dark streetcontinues.

It's difficult to feel safe in this corner of Thesden, where footstepsseem to echo ominously on this empty street.  The occasional disquietingscream of an alley cat or a person breaks the quiet of the street, where theonly other sounds are whispers from alleys and the soft shuffle of feetalong cobbles.  To the north is Falstaff Square, known as the slimyunderbelly of Thesden.

This looks like the kind of place your mother warned you to stay awayfrom.  Tell-tale rust red stains spatter the grey stones of this square,which might once have been as beautiful as Thesden's other squares.  Now,however, the statues are broken and covered in graffiti, and the fountainsdon't work.  You suspect the town militia doesn't see this place much.  Adark, narrow street leads off to the south.

The buildings along this square are almost all boarded up, abandoned orat least the residents want to make it appear that way.  What might oncehave been a statue stands on a paint covered pedestal, now just a pair offeet, broken off at the ankles.

The corner of the square has the one business present in the section oftown, `d'The Spider's Ring Tavern'`l, the sounds of drunken patrons pouringout of the door.  You feel quite unsafe with these shifty men watching youand the nearest guardsman 10 blocks away.

The remains of a stone fountain are here, now just a pool of brackishwater.  You have a pretty strong suspicion that Thesden's town militiadoesn't come to this square much.  Trash litters the square, blowing aroundin the breeze.

This wide avenue leads straight across town, reaching from the west gatealmost all the way to the east.  Used constantly by merchants and travelersheading to the center of town, the slate stones worn and cracked from athousand footsteps and wagon wheels.  The gate to Thesden can be seen justto the west.

The wide slate paving stones of the avenue are somewhat crumbled here,but an effort has been made to fill in the cracks with gravel.  Only a fewpeople walk by, usually moving quickly to the west gate or east towards thecenter of town.

This tavern appears to be the haunt of most of the younger town militiamen as well as a smattering of petty merchants.  The floor, walls and barare all made from a dark brown wood, giving the place a dim feel even withdaylight streaming in the windows.`lA brass plaque is mounted on the wall.``

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n enters the clothing shop, admiring the fine vestiments.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n brushes by some heavy woolen coats, and exits the clothing shop.
Rooms.RoomDescription: This small shop contains several racks of clothing made from cotton andwool, most of it appears fairly shapeless and aimed at the idea of 'one sizefits all'.  Set on a shelf on the side wall are a number of hats, rangingfrom fashionable to bizarre.  Behind the ash-wood counter are some veryexpensive brightly colored imported silk garments.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The bell rings as $n enters the shop.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The air swirls as the door closes behind $n.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The front room of this shop is richly decorated with velvet drapes andplush carpets.  Spread around the floor are chairs, desk, tables and bedsranging from utilitarian to luxury.  In the back room, behind a pinecounter, is a workshop where several craftsman are busy working with sawsand files.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Wary eyes turn to $n as $e enters the shop.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n is watched closely as $e walks out.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The windows to this small shop have heavy iron bars over them, and allthe merchandise is behind the counter safely away from reach.  The walls aremostly quite plain.  The wall behind the counter, however, glitters like thenight sky with gems, gold and silver.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n pushes aside the curtains and enters the shop, light streaming in behind $m.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n exits the shop through the curtains to the west, back into the bright light of the square.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Dim light falls through the burgandy curtains onto the cramped aisles ofthis shop.  The shelves are filled with sealed glass vails, each allowingonly the slightest odor to escape, yet the combined scent of a thousandspices makes you feel unsteady.

Rooms.EnterMsg: `kWith the jingling of many coins, `f$n `kglides in.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `kPockets bulging with gold, `f$n `kstrolls out.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: This pleasant office is the home of the Satin Purse, a merchants guilddedicated to protecting and promoting the interests of Thesden's merchants.No one appears to be working right now, the desks empty with neat piles ofpapers on each of them.

`lThe`o blinding`k glow`l of your sudden magical transferrence fades from yourvision.  As you look about your new surroundings you see that you are in alarge, rectangular stone room.  From the`i banners`l hanging from the rafters highabove you and from the spectacular view of Thesden laid out before you througha large, leaded window of diamond-shaped panes, you determine that you aresomewhere near the top of`a Dunluce Castle`l.  The chamber is bare, except forthe`i c`ko`jl`no`lr`mf`iu`kl`l standards above the long,`d oaken table`l beneath them.  Severalchairs in different shapes and sizes have been set at both sides of the tableand a large, ornate one sits at the table head, before the window.A massive set of thick, wooden doors with bands of`h iron`l across them standcloesd to the south.  A pair of palace guards dressed in`n g`ol`ne`oa`nm`oi`nn`og`h silver`l and`owhite`l prevent any unauthorized persons from entering or leaving.``

Rooms.EnterMsg: `oA dozen reflections of $n appear on shiny things as $e enters. ``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `nThe reflections of $n vanish as $e leaves.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: Glittering necklaces and bright, intricate figurines fill the glass casesalong the walls of this shop.  The work is mostly impractical and designedfor the nobility with nothing better to spend their money on, though it isstill quite beautiful.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The floor creaks under $n's footsteps as $e enters Town Hall.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wooden boards squeak as $n leaves Town Hall.
Rooms.RoomDescription: This wide hall looks welcoming, if somewhat plain compared with most ofThesden's architecture.  The well-swept floors are done in unfinished teak,worn with years of footsteps.  A staircase leads upwards, a neatly paintedsign at the bottom reads, 'Offices may be found Upstairs'.  A narrowentryway to the east leads to a Donation Room.  To the west, a frameddoorway contains the passageway to many wondrous lands, the Library.Travellers who are new to Exodus should look manifesto for a few hints tosurviving.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Through the gloom, the form of $n appears.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The shape of $n fades off into the darkness.
Rooms.RoomDescription: `bA few crimson candles cast a flickering glow over the shelves of theapothecary, which is probably for the best, you're better off not seeing theinventory in full daylight if you don't like nausea.  Barely identifiabledried animal parts, strange powders in tiny bags, and smoking liquids incrystal vials line the shelves.  `` ``

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n enters the inn, perhaps looking for company or just seeking shelter.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The old floor creaks and groans as $n takes $s leave.
Rooms.RoomDescription: A warm glow cast by the sooty black fireplace gives a homey feel to thissmall inn, particularily when compared to the dark square outside.  A creakywooden staircase leads to the rooms upstairs.  The patrons in the diningarea seem fairly reclusive and quiet, you feel like you should probablywhisper your order.

Rooms.EnterMsg: `aOut of nowhere, `h$n `asuddenly stands next to you.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `aThe space where `h$n `aused to stand is empty.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: The black walls of this building are seamless, wrought by magic from asingle piece of dark stone.  A silvery crescent moon lies inset into thewall, shining starkly bright against the darkness of the background.  Theorder has been the primary school for mages for many years, dedicated toteaching control of the mystical arts.  A spiral staircase leads upwards tothe higher levels of the order.
You stand in a short hallway, a painting of Dunluce castle hanging fromthe wall.  Three plain wooden doors are on the east, west and north walls,leading to the guest rooms of the inn.
The stairs end on a wide hardwood landing.  Doors to the rooms lead offto the east and west.  The landing is unfurnished and extremely neat, thefloors polished to shine.
This bedroom is barely furnished, besides the plain bed with grey sheetsthere is little of note.  A small window on the south wall lets in a thinbeam of light, dust clouds rolling through it.

The room is sparsely furnished, but the bed looks quite comfortable.  Alarge window to the south opens on the dark square below, and the face ofone of the gargoyles atop a nearby building peeks in the side, giving you astrong urge to draw the curtains.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The heavy iron door groans loudly as $n pushes it open.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The door abruptly clangs to a shut as $n leaves.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Waves of heat rolling off the furnace in the rear of the shop makes theheat in here nearly unbearable.  A number of hooks line the western wall,each holding a sample of iron-work; ranging from axes to hinges.  Thepiercing clang of hammer on molten iron rings through the room, making ithard to hear.

Rooms.EnterMsg: With aspirations of outdoor adventure, $n examines the images of nature on the walls.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n leaves the tranquility of this shop for the bustling square outside.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The decor in this shop gives you the impression that the proprietorspends a good deal more time painting wilderness from a safe distance ratherthan trying to survive in it.  For every rope, backpack and pick-axe thereis a painting of an ice-topped mountain, a frothing river, or a thick, darkforest.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Enticed by the aroma of exotic flowers, $n enters the shop.
Rooms.ExitMsg: While exiting the floral shop, $n almost knocks over a valuable vase.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Light pours into the shop through the white lace curtains, falling on astunning assortment of flowers.  Many of the flowers are in pots filled withrich, dark soil; others are kept in crystal vases, grouped by type andcolor.  Only a small counter at the back remains free of plants, a singlespot of brown in a humid mess of color.  A small sign by the counter reads,'sorry, there's no such thing as black orchids. '

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n walks in and imbibes in the scent of fresh berries.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n carefully maneuvers around a puddle on the way out.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The stand is made up of a collection of stopped carts, each filled withfruits and vegetables from the farms outside Thesden.  A leaky wooden roof,precariously balanced on four supports at the corners, covers the carts.Most of the produce looks fresh and tasty, if a little bruised.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Eyeing the meat hanging from the ceiling hungrily, $n strolls in.
Rooms.ExitMsg: Ignoring the squeals of a dying pig, $n exits the butcher shop.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The floor of this shop is covered in thin chips of cedar, not quiteoverpowering the odor of meat.  From large hooks hang whole sides of cow,pig, and a few un-plucked chickens.  Some sealed boxes behind the counterhave 'Salted Meats' written on them in large black letters.  The occasional'Baa' or 'Moo' from the rear of the shop gives you a clear idea just howfresh the meat is.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n steps onto the docks, causing them to sway gently.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The time-worn wood of the docks creaks and sways slightly with eachfootstep.  The masts of ships stand out among a forest of ropes to the eastand west.  A few ships with sails raised pull out heading to the open ocean,slowly shrinking to white dots on the horizon.

Rooms.EnterMsg: `kThe flames of a candle f`ol`ki`oc`kk`oe`kr as $n enters.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `kA candle is nearly `bblown out`k as $n walks past, leaving.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: Hanging on the walls of this tiny shop are colorful candles, smallbedside lamps, and powerful ship-lanterns.  Some impressive tiny waxsculptures of ships and knights attest to what Simon does to occupy hisspare time.  A price list hangs above the counter, lit by a hanging candlewhich drips sea-blue wax onto the floor.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Footsteps ring on the stone floor as $n walks in.
Rooms.ExitMsg: Footsteps echo throughout the cathedral as $n walks out.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The cathedral is awe-inspiring:  vaulted ceilings painted pure whitereflect sunlight and brighten the whole room.  Massive stained glass windowsfilled with scenes of sainted martyrs alight the walls.  Far to the east analtar can be seen upon a raised dias, before a tall obelisk of obsidian.

Rooms.EnterMsg: `mC`lo`nl`jo`kr`ie`md `olight `lshifts across $n as $e enters the shop.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `lThe `mc`lo`nl`jo`kr`ie`md `olight `lslides off of $n as $e walks out.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: A delicate rainbow of colored light fills this shop from the stainedglass windows and tinted lanterns.
